    Bean
        It is simply an object that is instantiated, assembled, and managed by the Spring IoC 
        (Inversion of Control) container.
    
    The XML Configuration / Annotations: The instructions you give to the factory.
    The Spring Container: The actual automated factory.

    Why use Beans instead of the new keyword?
        The new keyword means you are responsible for creating, linking, and destroying objects.
        Spring Beans mean Spring manages the objects, links them together automatically, and saves 
        memory by sharing them.
    
